You either a) Still have a RealPlume folder in GameData, b) Did not remove the RealPlume-Stock folder when you uninstalled, or c) Have some other mod that uses FOR[RealPlume] instead of NEEDS[RealPlume,SmokeScreen] in it's patches.

The existence of an empty RealPlume folder, or the use of FOR[RealPlume] in a patch will trick mods into thinking RealPlume is installed.

3 hours ago, zakkpaz said:

for B9 partswitch is there a way to edit the .cfg so it applies to the vanilla parts?

If you like B9 then Nertea's CryoEngines mod would be your best bet. It's fairly lightweight and adds fuel switching to all tanks. It includes the necessary code to avoid colliding with other mods that also use fuel switching.

1 minute ago, Jso said:

You either a) Still have a RealPlume folder in GameData, b) Did not remove the RealPlume-Stock folder when you uninstalled, or c) Have some other mod that uses FOR[RealPlume] instead of NEEDS[RealPlume,SmokeScreen] in it's patches.

The existence of an empty RealPlume folder, or the use of FOR[RealPlume] in a patch will trick mods into thinking RealPlume is installed.

Definitely don't have any realplume installed at all. Option C, is completely possible though. I found the HOYO CM and LEM mods were doing the same as well, and deleting his RP config files fixed those engines as well, so at least that is an easy fix, instead of trying to locate which mod is causing it. Thanks for the answer though. At least I know what is most likely the cause of it if I ever do want to track down the problem.
